{
  "texts": [
    "As the overall number of missing responses was low (6.9% of the 3,708 × 38 matrix of numbers), it was decided to impute these missing values, approximately preserving the means and intercorrelations between item responses.",
    "Specifically, missing data were imputed using the nearest-neighbor method, whereby the missing data in the 3,708 respondents × 38 questions matrix were imputed with the value of the nearest-neighbor row according to the Euclidean distance.",
    "The mean scores on the 38 questions were interpreted to describe key patterns.",
    "Following this, the data (3,708 × 38 matrix of numbers) were subjected to exploratory maximum likelihood factor analysis.",
    "This statistical method aims to explain the correlations among variables by identifying latent factors that influence these variables; it is frequently used in the analysis of questionnaire data to reveal underlying psychological constructs (41)."
  ]
}